Its certainly possible.

Many years ago, I did that with H1 by starting the crawl up from
the command line, with jmx, from cron.

Then, the fine cron job checks if the crawl is done, issues the jmx
to shutdown.    Set whatever interval you like on such checking.

Then, start again.  And don&#39;t forget to do something clever with your warcs
you wrote, organizing carefully.

I don&#39;t even have those scripts anymore, it was at a private company, so 
I won&#39;t
send them to you.

John


